This paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of cryptocurrencies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data analysis and database management, which could be categorized under databases (cs.DB) and computer networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the study of distributed systems and algorithms, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the usage of cryptocurrencies for criminal activities, which could be categorized under cybercrime (cs.CY).
